listings.description:
For sale, brand new Hofner twin pickup hollow body bass with brand new Hofner hard shell case. Selling because I am now retired, and I need the money and have too many bass guitars.

My son just bought for me a Gibson EB-0, to go with my EB-2 Gibson semi hollow body bass.

This Les-shaped model is commonly named as the "Club bass."

With authentic details inspired by the original, the Hofner Icon Series Vintage Bass makes the legendary Club bass available to the rest of us.

Don't get the idea that this a just a "nowhere man" look-alike. This quality instrument features a real spruce top and beautiful flamed maple back and sides.

The hollow body and set neck will give you the warm, round tone you expect from the Club bass.  

this model features a maple set neck with rosewood fretboard accentuated by mother-of-pearl dot inlays, the signature Höfner violin bass headstock,

 a trapeze tailpiece, and glossy spruce top with glossy flamed maple back and sides. An ebony bridge with movable metal saddles maintains intonation and string spacing.

The nickel-plated hardware and floating celluloid pearl pickguard give it an extra little pop for the eyes.

On the electronics side, you're working with two original Höfner humbucking pickups, as well as a control panel with 2 volume controls, 2 on/off switches, and a rhythm/solo switch for volume boost.

The overall sound is warm like the original model, but with a little more sonic kick for a more "now" sound. 

Hofner Ignition Series Vintage Club Bass Features:

  • Authentic details inspired by the original
  • Spruce top
  • Flamed maple back and sides
  • Set neck
  • Rosewood fretboard
  • 30" scale
  • 22 frets
  • Dot inlay
  • Weight 4.90 Lbs

listings.description:
For sale is a customized 2007 Ibanez Prestige RG2570E (Ibanez Prestige RG1570 body) in great condition, with a hardshell case (which has a built-in tuner). This Made in Japan guitar plays and sounds great.

The upgraded Dimarzio pickups (Air Norton neck, AT-1 Andy Timmons bridge) are versatile, especially with the 5-way super switch.

The tremolo block has been upgraded to a tapered FU-Tone brass block, increasing sustain and producing a richer tone, while also allowing for full tremolo dive up and down.

This clean, quality Ibanez Prestige is currently set up with D’Addario 10-46 strings for standard tuning and low action. The guitar has some light surface scratches and some fret wear (the frets have much life left).

The hardshell case’s handle is detached (though included).

GUITAR HISTORY

I purchased this RG2570E new in 2007. Later in 2007, I refinished the factory Vital Silver textured body and black headstock in color changing paint (rust to green). I applied an aftermarket silver Ibanez decal to the headstock prior to the clearcoat (following the paint and black primer layers). In 2008, I replaced the body with that of an Ibanez Prestige 1570 in Mirage Blue (blue, green, & purple sparkle fibers).

After replacing the body, I added the green mirror pickguard, Dimarzio pickups, and a 5-way Fender superswitch.


Included with the guitar and case:

  • Original tremolo bar
  • Original Ibanez Edge Pro 6 tremolo block
  • 7mm truss rod adjustment wrench
  • 3mm hex wrench for the pressure pads, bridge height adjustment, and string locking/unlocking at the saddles
  • 2mm hex wrench for saddle intonation adjustment
  • Installed Dunlop straplocks (entire system included)
  • Original strap buttons
  • Strap (ESP Guitars brand, leather)
  • Bronze mirror HSH pickguard (I had a middle single on the guitar for some time – the RG1570 body is factory routed for the HSH configuration)

The Mega Man/Hulk sticker on the truss rod cover is removable.

 

SPECIFICATIONS 

MODEL: RG2570E Prestige (RG1570 Prestige body)

YEAR: 2007

MADE IN: Japan

BODY: Basswood

BODY COLOR: Mirage Blue, gloss finish

NECK JOINT: All Access Neck Joint

SCALE LENGTH: 25.5”/648mm

NECK: Wizard Prestige 5-piece Maple/Walnut (43mm nut width, 18mm thickness at 1st fret, 20mm thickness at 12th fret), satin finish

FRETBOARD MATERIAL: Rosewood with white binding and silver wedge sharktooth inlays

FRETBOARD RADIUS: 430mm

FRETS: 24 jumbo

BRIDGE: Edge Pro 6 (with upgraded FU-Tone tapered brass tremolo block)

PICKUPS: Dimarzio Air Norton DP293 (neck) and Dimarzio AT-1 Andy Timmons DP224 (bridge)

ELECTRONICS: 1 volume, 1 tone, 5-way switch (full neck, outside coils, full neck + full bridge, inside coils, full bridge)

TUNING MACHINES: Gotoh

HARDWARE COLOR: Cosmo Black

listings.description:
In perfect working order.  I've just decided to handle drums outside of the modular synth case. 

"Introducing the BD808, part of our new series of drum modules that brings analog percussion into the modular synth world, instantly turning your system into a self-contained music machine. Its small size, minimalist design and modern production methods have allowed us to bring the world’s most famous bass drum sound generator back at a very low cost. The real thing is here again.

The BD808 is the Roland TR-808’s Bass Drum circuit adapted for use in Eurorack format and tuned to sound like a machine that come fresh off the original 80’s assembly line. The adaption to modular format has allowed us to add some special features like independent Accent level, a high-powered gain stage, dual input pulse-shaper and extended decay; all without compromising the signature sound of the TR-808."
listings.title: Tiptop Audio BD808 Eurorack Bass Drum 2017 Silver
